  <h3><a name="news">Latest News</a></h3>

  <ul>
    <li><p><b>12 November, 2006</b> : The very first install ISO
     and live CD can be downloaded from here: <a
     href="http://people.freebsd.org/~jb/sun4v/7.0-20061112-SNAP-sun4v-disc1.iso.bz2">
     7.0-20061112-SNAP-sun4v-disc1.iso.bz2</a>.</p>

     <p>You will notice a number of acd0 timeouts during boot. These will be
     fixed in a later version. For now, just be patient.</p>

     <p>To use the live CD, use the 'Fixit' menu item. Note that this is
     a snapshot, so there will be a warning about the label not matching
     7.0-CURRENT.</p>
  </ul>

  <h3><a name="hw">Hardware List</a></h3>

  <p>A summary of supported systems follows.  SMP is supported on all supported
    systems.</p>

  <ul>
    <li><a href="http://www.sun.com/servers/coolthreads/t1000/">Sun Fire T1000 Server</a></li>
    <li><a href="http://www.sun.com/servers/coolthreads/t2000/">Sun Fire T2000 Server</a></li>
 </ul>

  <h3><a name="todo">What Needs To Be Done</a></h3>

  <ul>
    <li>Load balance interrupts between CPUs.</li>
    <li>Add support for the serial port.</li>
    <li>System date and time. Use ntpdate in the mean time.</li>
  </ul>

